Labelled Transition System

Generalization of Automata

$$(X,A, \rightarrow)$$

$$X$$ is a set of states

$$A$$ is a set of actions (alphabet)

$$\rightarrow \in X \times A \times X$$ (transition relation)

$$(x,a,y) \in  \rightarrow $$ Becomes $$x \xrightarrow{a} y$$

No initial state or acceptance
